      <h1>Welcome, friend</h1>

      <p>mountebank provides multi-protocol, multi-language test doubles over the wire.
      Learning mountebank couldn't be easier.  Start off simply by using this website.
      The key domain concept is an <dfn>imposter</dfn>, which represents a test double.
      The only thing you need to do is give an imposter a port and pick a protocol,
      and mountebank will provide you access to all requests to that imposter.  If you
      want stubbing as well, mountebank provides for you a rich set of stubbing
      primitives.</p>

      <p>Once you're satisfied that mountebank is for you, simply <code>npm install -g mb</code>.
      mountebank has been tested with node.js 0.8 and 0.10.  Then, a simple <code>mb</code> will
      get you going.</p>

      <p>mountebank is still a work in progress.  Not all protocols are implemented yet, and
      native language bindings are still being worked on.  Fear not, friend, for mountebank has
      a team of open source developers, and they are legion.</p>

