      <h2>Why mountebank?</h2>

      <p>There are many other tools, some of them quite good, that will provide HTTP stubbing.
      Some of them don't actually go over the wire, instead relying on faking on some low-level
      network libraries.  As such, they are forever tied to the language in which they are
      implemented in.  Others rely on loading the stubbing setup through a configuration file.
      This means your tests are forced to depend on significant setup external to the test code
      itself, and that you cannot make mock-style verifications on certain HTTP calls.</p>

      <p>None of them support multiple protocols.  None of them support multiple native language
      bindings.</p>

